&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://dinersclubofferstool.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/APAC-AUCKLAND-SIDART-OFFER-LOGO.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-7209&quot; src=&quot;http://dinersclubofferstool.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/APAC-AUCKLAND-SIDART-OFFER-LOGO.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;APAC- AUCKLAND- SIDART- OFFER- LOGO&quot; width=&quot;135&quot; height=&quot;75&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
From the small, elegantly designed dining room with a view onto the Auckland skyline, Sidart is a hidden gem that has gained world acclaim, earning a spot on the Diners Club International Global Selection, Cuisine Magazine&rsquo;s Good Food Guide 2014 Restaurant of the Year and 3 Hats, and Metro Magazine Best Fine Dining Restaurant. A chef&rsquo;s table for four to six people allows guests to see the kitchen action and interact with the chefs. Menus change constantly which allows for creativity according to concept ideas, inspiration and the week by week changes in market availability. Ponsonby neighborhood. Smart casual attire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diners Club cardmembers enjoy&nbsp;a complimentary signature dish of Roquefort Cheesecake, Roquefort ice-cream, red wine jelly, pear and almond per guest as well as a priority reservation for the Chef&amp;#8217;s table and a chef-signed copy of the menu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please book online at Sidart &lt;a title=&quot;Sidart Reservations&quot; href=&quot;http://www.sidart.co.nz/page/reservations/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;website&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;or contact by phone at +64-9-360-2122 or email at reservations@sidart.co.nz to book your reservation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mention Diners Club International Privileges Dining Collection to receive your special benefit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide your name, date you would like to dine, number of guests, preferred time, cell phone or local (hotel) phone number and your personal email address. A credit card will be required at the time of booking to hold your reservation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cancellation Policy- Should you need to cancel your reservation or reduce the numbers in your party, you must give at least 24 hours&rsquo; notice. Failure to cancel will incur a cancellation/no-show fee of $100 per person cancelled for dinner reservations and $50 for lunch reservations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconfirmation Policy: Please contact the restaurant by phone or email 24 hours prior to your dining date to reconfirm. Reservations that are not confirmed may be forfeited. Provide a reminder that this is a Diners Club International Privileges Dining Collection reservation. If not reconfirmed your reservation may be given away if need arises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TERMS &amp;amp; CONDITIONS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow booking instructions to ensure receiving your Privileges Dining Collection amenity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based on Availability at the time of booking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Menu is tasting/degustation only&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your Privileges Dining Collection benefit may not be combined with other offers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fulfillment of the offer is the sole responsibility of the participating restaurant merchant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Restaurant participation and benefits are subject to change or cancellation without notice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

